title.narrative: 104 DEMAND GENERATION AND SOCIAL NORMS FOR HEALTH

description.narrative: By 2022, government and partners have enhanced capacity to generate demand for adoption of positive health practices supported by preventive and responsive health services that improve the health and wellbeing of children and adolescents, which contributes to Child Health, Child Health (Covid), Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Immunization. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Business and Key Business Stakeholders demonstrate growing willingness, commitment and resource allocation for protecting and promoting child rights in policy and practice by 2022
